```py
p = 2^255-19
E = EllipticCurve(GF(p),[0,486662,0,1,0])
f = lambda x: x^3 + 486662 * x^2 + x
y_2 = f(Zmod(p)(9))
print(y_2)
y = (Zmod(p)(y_2).sqrt(extend=false, all = true))
print(y)
G = E(9, y[0])
Q = 0x1337c0decafe* G
print(Q)
```
